# Trivy ignore file — each suppression MUST be justified.
# Only architectural false-positives belong here. Real CVEs are intentionally
# left visible so a rebuild picks up fixes once upstream (Debian) ships them.

# DS-0002: "Specify at least 1 USER command in Dockerfile with non-root user"
# False positive given our gosu pattern. The container starts as root solely so
# docker-entrypoint.sh can `chown -R couchpotato:couchpotato /config /data`
# (mounted volumes can't be chowned at build time), then immediately drops
# privileges with `exec gosu couchpotato ...`. The application never runs as
# root. A static `USER couchpotato` would break runtime volume-permission fixup.
DS-0002
